//// 2. Proposed annotation for fertility
//// Description: Soil ability to supply nutrients (ratings 0-1).
//// Note: The 'classes' column maps integer codes (0-10) to value ranges (0.0-0.1, etc.).
//// We discretize these codes into the midpoint of each range (e.g., 1 -> 0.05).
//// Codes 11-14 represent non-soil features (steep slopes, water) and are mapped to unknown.
//model 'local:alessio.bulckaen:im.data.global:ecdc__soil__fertility__global__2001_2020'
//	as soil.incubation:SoilFertilityType classified into
//  	soil.incubation:Infertile if (0 1 2),
//	soil.incubation:LowFertility if (3 4),
//	soil.incubation:ModerateFertility if (5 6 7),
//	soil.incubation:HighFertility if (8 9 10)
//over space(shape="POLYGON ((180 -90, 180 90, -180 90, -180 -90, 180 -90))");
////	soil.incubation:SteepTerrainSlope if (11),
////	soil.incubation:PermafrostGalcier if (12); 
//   
////  discretized into 
////    0 if 0,             // Value 0
////    0.05 if 1,          // Range 0.0-0.1
////    0.15 if 2,          // Range 0.1-0.2
////    0.25 if 3,          // Range 0.2-0.3
////    0.35 if 4,          // Range 0.3-0.4
////    0.45 if 5,          // Range 0.4-0.5
////    0.55 if 6,          // Range 0.5-0.6
////    0.65 if 7,          // Range 0.6-0.7
////    0.75 if 8,          // Range 0.7-0.8
////    0.85 if 9,          // Range 0.8-0.9
////    0.95 if 10;         // Range 0.9-1.0
////    unknown if 11,      // Steep_terrain_slopes
////    unknown if 12,      // Permafrost_Glacier
////    unknown if 13,      // Miscellaneous_Unit_No_information
////    unknown if 14;      // Water
//
//// 3. Proposed annotation for nitrogen
//// Description: Concentration of nitrogen in the soil.
//// Concept: Modeled as a proportion (mass fraction) of Nitrogen within Soil.
//// Note: Unit g/kg [1] is compatible with the proportion operator [625].
